        "timestamp": "2023-05-09 09:29:33.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-2\n\n1. \nget_input should not be in the generated tosca, i.e. \n\n          $get_input_ext:\n          - get_input:\n            - cds_model_name\n\nshould be\n\n          $get_input_ext:\n          - cds_model_name\n\n2.\nonly inputs (and sub properties of inputs) that match the type of the property being set should be displayed (in the same way as is done for get_input). At the moment all inputs are available for selection irrespective of type\n\n3.\nWhen get_input_ext is selected a superfluous box surrounds the input - it should be presented the same as if get_input was selected",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
